         <abstract>
            <p>Let GF(p&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;/sup&gt;) be the finite field with p&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;/sup&gt; elements, where p is prime. We consider the problem of how to deterministically generate in polynomial time a subset of GF(p&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;/sup&gt;) that contains a primitive root, i.e., an element that generates the multiplicative group of nonzero elements in GF(p&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;/sup&gt;). We present three results. First, we present a solution to this problem for the case where p is small, i.e., p = n&lt;sup&gt;O(1)&lt;/sup&gt;. Second, we present a solution to this problem under the assumption of the Extended Riemann Hypothesis (ERH) for the case where p is large and n = 2. Third, we give a quantitative improvement of a theorem of Wang on the least primitive root for GF(p), assuming the ERH.</p>
          </abstract>
